      "lesson title": "AI in Film Production Workflows",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces you to the ways artificial intelligence is being used across film production workflows, with a particular focus on editing, visual effects, and automated production tools. You will explore how AI-powered software is changing the day-to-day roles of editors, VFX artists, and producers, and what that means for the people working in these areas. Along the way, we will look at the practical risks that come with relying on automated systems, including issues around creative control, data accuracy, and the potential for errors in finished work. No prior technical knowledge is required, as the lesson is designed to give you a clear and grounded understanding of where AI fits into modern film production. By the end, you will have a solid foundation for thinking critically about how these tools are used responsibly within the industry.",
